## 5. Variant B (FROZEN — properly specified this time)

For Phase β, Variant B applies *only* to slot 15. Every other slot is set-derived or single-point-derived and is structurally invariant under route permutation — variant B and variant A produce the same value by construction. Route-invariance is now slot 15's responsibility alone.

This is a Phase α correction: Phase α's pre-registry §4 implied variant B would run "the four-form battery in a different order" *for every slot*, but most slots aren't order-sensitive. Phase β scopes variant B precisely.

